Bank of America Corp Ending Credit Protection Services-Reuters
Tuesday, 21 Aug 2012 06:24pm EDT
Reuters reported that Bank of America Corp will stop selling credit protection services which were the subject of a class action suit in which customers alleged they were charged without their permission and enrolled through deceptive practices. A $20 million settlement of the lawsuit received preliminary court approval last month but still needs final approval.Â 
